    <chapter title="Glossary" id="glossary">
        <p>Here is a breakdown of terms used in this article:</p>
        <deflist>
            <def title="Credit">
                Each message or edit stored in our database uses 1 credit. These are non-refundable once used, even if the message or backup is deleted.
            </def>
            <def title="(ST) Credits">
                Server Transferable Credits. These are credits which can only be transferred to a server pot. I.e. they cannot be given to another user.
            </def>
            <def title="Server Pot">
                This is the collective pot of credits that sparkles! will take from for each message backed up. Credits cannot be removed from the pot by anyone, including whoever bought them.
            </def>
        </deflist>
    </chapter>
